{"changes": [{"date_iso": "2026-06-06", "date_label": "Sat.06.06.26", "description": {"new": "The night moves through early\nDetroit\ntechno\nand\nBerlin dub techno\nwith\nFadi Mohem\nand\nMarcel Dettmann\n, delivering a sound rooted in reduction, repetition and forward momentum. Long blends, rolling grooves and subtle shifts in intensity shape the flow of the night from start to finish.\nBarulho World returns to Annex, bringing a curated night to Dortmund that moves between club culture and global sonic landscapes.\n\nAs a collective, Barulho World stands for a perspective on\nelectronic music that centers Afro-diasporic influences\nand connects local scenes with international currents.\n\nThe musical focus lies on\nAfro-electronic sounds\nin their full range: from Afrohouse and\nAfrotech\nto\nGqom\n,\nBaile Funk\nand\nKuduro\n, extending into genre-crossing hybrid forms. Rather than fixed categories, the emphasis is on music as a connecting force.\n\nA key part of this approach is the integration of live and hybrid elements. Through hardware, performative setups, or voice, the music remains immediate and closely tied to the moment. The dancefloor becomes not only a space for listening, but for experiencing performance itself.\n\nWith Frau Beji, Piccell and D[Nowhere]J, different perspectives come together, each embodying this approach and shaping the space both sonically and emotionally.\n\nAdmission 25 €", "old": "Barulho World returns to Annex, bringing a curated night to Dortmund that moves between club culture and global sonic landscapes.\n\nAs a collective, Barulho World stands for a perspective on\nelectronic music that centers Afro-diasporic influences\nand connects local scenes with international currents.\n\nThe musical focus lies on\nAfro-electronic sounds\nin their full range: from Afrohouse and\nAfrotech\nto\nGqom\n,\nBaile Funk\nand\nKuduro\n, extending into genre-crossing hybrid forms. Rather than fixed categories, the emphasis is on music as a connecting force.\n\nA key part of this approach is the integration of live and hybrid elements. Through hardware, performative setups, or voice, the music remains immediate and closely tied to the moment. The dancefloor becomes not only a space for listening, but for experiencing performance itself.\n\nWith Frau Beji, Piccell and D[Nowhere]J, different perspectives come together, each embodying this approach and shaping the space both sonically and emotionally.\n\nAdmission 25 €"}, "fields": {}, "floor_changes": [], "floor_subtitle_changes": [], "floors_added": [], "floors_removed": [], "id": "2026-06-06", "kind": "modified", "slot_changes": [], "title": null, "url": "https://www.openground.club/en/schedule/2026-06-06"}, {"date_iso": "2026-06-13", "date_label": "Sat.13.06.26", "description": {"new": "A night shaped by\nexperimental Detroit techno\n, genre-bending selections and a steady awareness of the dancefloor. Moving from hypnotic and stripped-back\ntechno\ninto\nhouse\n,\njungle\nand raw machine-driven rhythms.\nFor nearly ten years,\nCallshop Radio\nhas been broadcasting live to the world. What began in a backyard in Düsseldorf as part of the interdisciplinary cultural space ROOOOOM has, over the years, evolved into an established community radio, building studios in Leipzig, Paris, and Vienna. The\ndiversity of genres\nreflects the many facets of the scenes that Callshop Radio calls home.\n\nAlongside its ongoing radio program, events have always been a core part of the collective. Collaborations with festivals, clubs, museums, and concert venues create opportunities to bring the station’s hosts onto the stage beyond the studio. The focus remains on connecting artists from different locations and shaping events collaboratively.\n\nOn June 13, the radio stays true to this vision: for the Annex Floor at Open Ground, alongside one guest and two residents from the Düsseldorf and Leipzig locations have been invited.\n\nAdmission 25 €", "old": "For nearly ten years, Callshop Radio has been broadcasting live to the world. What began in a backyard in Düsseldorf as part of the interdisciplinary cultural space ROOOOOM has, over the years, evolved into an established community radio, building studios in Leipzig, Paris, and Vienna. The diversity of genres reflects the many facets of the scenes that Callshop Radio calls home.\n\nAlongside its ongoing radio program, events have always been a core part of the collective. Collaborations with festivals, clubs, museums, and concert venues create opportunities to bring the station’s hosts onto the stage beyond the studio. The focus remains on connecting artists from different locations and shaping events collaboratively.\n\nOn June 13, the radio stays true to this vision: for the Annex Floor at Open Ground, alongside one guest and two residents from the Düsseldorf and Leipzig locations have been invited.\n\nAdmission 25 €"}, "fields": {}, "floor_changes": [], "floor_subtitle_changes": [], "floors_added": [], "floors_removed": [], "id": "2026-06-13", "kind": "modified", "slot_changes": [], "title": null, "url": "https://www.openground.club/en/schedule/2026-06-13"}, {"date_iso": "2026-06-20", "date_label": "Sat.20.06.26", "description": {"new": "Freifeld begins with a\nDub-Set\nby Tasha and Stojche, before moving between\ndeep house\n,\ntechno\nand\nbass-informed\nclub music. Sensual vocal-led house, raw vinyl-driven techno rooted in Detroit, and\nUK bass\n,\nbreaks\nand\njungle\nunfold in fluid sets shaped by a music-first attitude and an unpolished underground energy.\nThis night, Annex will be rooted in\nDIY soundsystem culture\nand\ndeep bass\n. Moving between dub, steppers, broken UK rhythms, experimental electronics and 4x4 basslines, shaped by a collective approach to selection and a strong focus on low frequencies and community energy.\n\nAdmission 20 € / before 23:00 15 €", "old": null}, "fields": {}, "floor_changes": [], "floor_subtitle_changes": [], "floors_added": [], "floors_removed": [], "id": "2026-06-20", "kind": "modified", "slot_changes": [], "title": null, "url": "https://www.openground.club/en/schedule/2026-06-20"}, {"date_iso": "2026-06-27", "date_label": "Sat.27.06.26", "description": {"new": "Experimental\nelectronics\n,\ndub\n,\ntechno\nand sound-based performance. Shaped by a focus on sound as material, spatial thinking and deep listening, the night unfolds between club energy and more abstract, research-driven sonic forms.\nA night moving between\nhouse\n,\ntechno\n,\nelectro\nand\nbreaks\n, connecting scenes from the Ruhr area, Berlin, Cologne and beyond. From driving, groovy techno and acid- and synth-driven sounds to hypnotic, break- and house-influenced sets, the evening unfolds as a continuous flow between club energy, live elements and experimental sound forms.\nAdmission 20 € / before 23:00 15 €", "old": "Admission 20 € / before 23:00 15 €"}, "fields": {}, "floor_changes": [], "floor_subtitle_changes": [], "floors_added": [], "floors_removed": [], "id": "2026-06-27", "kind": "modified", "slot_changes": [], "title": null, "url": "https://www.openground.club/en/schedule/2026-06-27"}], "run_at": "2026-05-27T13:36:09+00:00"}
